<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-8212] KStreams documentation Maven artifact table is cut off</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8212</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the &lt;a href=&quot;https://kafka.apache.org/21/documentation/streams/developer-guide/write-streams.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Writing a Streams Application doc&lt;/a&gt;, the section &quot;LIBRARIES AND MAVEN ARTIFACTS&quot; has a table that lists out the Maven artifacts. The items in the group ID overflow and are cut off by the table column, even on a very large monitor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that &quot;artifact ID&quot; seems to have its word break property set correctly. See the attached image.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
