&lt;p&gt;   *&lt;b&gt;Jira ticket&lt;/b&gt;*: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8212&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8212&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fixed the table from cutting off the text by changing the table class to `datatable` (re-using a style that was already in the CSS and has an `overflow` property set).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This isn&apos;t the ideal fix. Given the current CSS, the `&amp;lt;pre&amp;gt;` items &lt;em&gt;should&lt;/em&gt; have a horizontal scroll, but they don&apos;t. If the entries in the first column of this table get too long, it will cut off the final column text. I tried several strategies, and nothing seemed to work. Can revisit if I have more time, this should work for now.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Fixed these versions, where I found the problem (let me know if there are other instances of it): `22`, `21`, `11`, `10`&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


